  "body": "- [ ] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nthe test helper function `assert.isAddress` seems to always throw an `TypeError: number.equals is not a function` error\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nin a test case, using the `isAddress` assertion will throw the error. e.g.\r\n\r\n```js\r\ncontract(\"SomeContractName\", accounts => {\r\n  it(\"should allow us to reproduce isAddress issue\", () => {\r\n    assert.isAddress(accounts[0])\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nit should pass when the input is a normal address, and report when the input is not an address. In no case should it report \"TypeError: number.equals is not a function\"\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nusing the function will report the following \r\n```\r\n1) Contract: SomeContractName\r\n       should allow us to reproduce isAddress issue:\r\n     TypeError: number.equals is not a function\r\n      at Assertion.<anonymous> (node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/core/lib/assertions.js:18:1)\r\n      at Assertion.propertyGetter (node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/node_modules/chai/lib/chai/utils/addProperty.js:62:1)\r\n      at Reflect.get (<anonymous>)\r\n      at Object.proxyGetter [as get] (node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/node_modules/chai/lib/chai/utils/proxify.js:98:1)\r\n      at Function.assert.isAddress (node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/core/lib/assertions.js:24:1)\r\n      at Context.<anonymous> (test/store.js:29:12)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Extra Information\r\n\r\nI didn't have experience with this repository (or it's dependency), but just from reading the stack trace and source code on github, the error seems to be coming from the following file [https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/56d22d731bad43d4b945565af54a266cdf6b1723/packages/core/lib/assertions.js#L16-L18](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/56d22d731bad43d4b945565af54a266cdf6b1723/packages/core/lib/assertions.js#L16-L18)\r\nwhich get the \"number\" from calling `toBN` from the package \"web3-utils\", which should return an `BN` instance from the package \"bn.js\". From reading the doc in it's readme, `BN` uses `eq` to test for equality instead of `equals`.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Arch linux\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache (cli)\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.5.2 (core: 5.5.2)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v17.4.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 8.3.1\r\n",
