    "body": "Hey @ASmallPotato, `assert` comes from the npm package chai. `isAddress` is not a chai method and the concept of an Ethereum address has no meaning in JavaScript unless you are using a package specifically designed for this.\r\n\r\nYou may be trying to use Truffle's testing Solidity library `Assert.sol` which is only available if you are writing Solidity tests. That has some functionality where you can do something like `Assert.address(<someValue>)`. You can find some docs about using this library on our website [here](https://trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/testing/writing-tests-in-solidity/). ",
